SIMPLE: embroidery
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embroidery
<hw>Em*broid"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Embroideries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Needlework used to enrich textile fabrics, leather, etc.; also, the
art of embroidering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Diversified ornaments, especially by contrasted
figures and colors; variegated decoration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fields in spring's <qex>embroidery</qex> are dressed.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A mere rhetorical <qex>embroidery</qex> of phrases.</q>
<rj><qau>J. A. Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embroil</ent>⟦br⟧
